HEADWORD: Treenail
<hw>Tree"nail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Tree +
nail.]</ety> <fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>A long wooden pin used in
fastening the planks of a vessel to the timbers or to each other.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>trenail</asp>, and
<asp>trunnel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

